description.narrative: UNICEF led the advocacy and support to countries for restoring immunization services safely during the COVID-19 pandemic, maintaining the organization’s global leadership in Vaccine Preventable Diseases (VPD) control, elimination and eradication. This included support to country and regional offices to protect progress, introduce new vaccines for children and adolescents and expand the reach of national immunization programmes for underserved communities. The immunization supply chain;unit led the improvement of national systems and immunization services while demonstrating how immunization provides a strong foundation for integrated PHC that could contribute to nearly half of the missing gap in achieving under-five mortality reduction. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/03/2022
